Sentencas: Single-step synthesis and deposition of composite solid oxide fuel cell cathodes of composition (Nd,Gd)(1/3)Sr2/3CoO3-delta : Ce-0.9(Gd,Nd)(0.1)O-1.95 (70 : 30 w : w) with and without the addition of Ag nanoparticles (Ag NPs) was achieved employing spray pyrolysis and low-temperature sintering at 900 degree celsius.
Titulo: Optimisation of the electrochemical performance of (Nd,Gd)1/3Sr2/3CoO3-δ cathode for solid oxide fuel cells via spray-pyrolysis deposition and decoration with Ag nanoparticles

Sentencas: Spray-pyrolysis-prepared materials offered improved microstructure with smaller particle size and higher porosity (extended triple phase boundary) in comparison to slurry-coated electrodes of analogous composition.
Titulo: Optimisation of the electrochemical performance of (Nd,Gd)1/3Sr2/3CoO3-δ cathode for solid oxide fuel cells via spray-pyrolysis deposition and decoration with Ag nanoparticles

Sentencas: Impedance spectroscopy of symmetrical cells of the composite air electrodes indicated a lower resistive response of the spray-pyrolysis-prepared electrodes with lower overall polarisation resistance (Rp), attributable to improved oxygen surface exchange and oxide-ion diffusion processes.
Titulo: Optimisation of the electrochemical performance of (Nd,Gd)1/3Sr2/3CoO3-δ cathode for solid oxide fuel cells via spray-pyrolysis deposition and decoration with Ag nanoparticles

Sentencas: Further reduction in Rp was achieved on decoration of the composite air electrodes with Ag NPs; the decorated composites were characterised by high resolution transmission electron microscopy (HRTEM) and high-angle annular dark-field scanning transmission electron microscopy (HAADF-STEM).
Titulo: Optimisation of the electrochemical performance of (Nd,Gd)1/3Sr2/3CoO3-δ cathode for solid oxide fuel cells via spray-pyrolysis deposition and decoration with Ag nanoparticles

Sentencas: Ag K-edge X-ray Absorption Near Edge Structure (XANES) and Extended X-ray Absorption Fine Structure (EXAFS) of Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-delta:Ag spray-pyrolysed composites indicated that the Ag nanoparticles exhibit a core-shell structure with a Ag2O outer layer calculated to be two unit cells in thickness.
Titulo: Optimisation of the electrochemical performance of (Nd,Gd)1/3Sr2/3CoO3-δ cathode for solid oxide fuel cells via spray-pyrolysis deposition and decoration with Ag nanoparticles

Sentencas: The outer particle shell is suggested to participate in the enhanced electrochemical response, lowering the electrode polarisation response of symmetrical cells below 700 degree celsius.
Titulo: Optimisation of the electrochemical performance of (Nd,Gd)1/3Sr2/3CoO3-δ cathode for solid oxide fuel cells via spray-pyrolysis deposition and decoration with Ag nanoparticles

Sentencas: Anode-supported single-cell fuel cells corresponding to the composite air electrode with Ag NPs and a thin YSZ-CGO electrolyte provided a maximum power density of 0.6 W cm(-2 )at 700 degree celsius.
Titulo: Optimisation of the electrochemical performance of (Nd,Gd)1/3Sr2/3CoO3-δ cathode for solid oxide fuel cells via spray-pyrolysis deposition and decoration with Ag nanoparticles
